            <title>[HBASE-16685] Revisit execution of SnapshotCopy in MapReduceBackupCopyService</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16685</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During code review of backup / restore, Matteo raised comment on the following code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        res = snapshotCp.run(options);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think this will be a first time where HBase server has a direct dependency on a MR job.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;also we need to revisit this code to avoid having one handler blocked for N hours while we are doing a copy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue is to address the above comment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
